This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category as it proposes a regularization technique to improve the training stability of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs). The paper also discusses the problem of missing modes in GANs, which is a common issue in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper introduces mathematical concepts related to probability distributions, which are relevant to the fields of neural networks (cs.NE) and graphics (cs.GR).
